comments: Green (DAL) is firming up over his left foot and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick on Banchero (ORL).
Anthony (ORL) avoids making contact with Green's (DAL) right arm as Green passes at the end of the drive.
Lively II (DAL) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Suggs (ORL) initiates contact with the back of Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) head during Hardaway Jr.'s jump shot attempt.
Williams (DAL) and Wagner (ORL) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Doncic (DAL) legally contests Banchero's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Anthony (ORL) and Green (DAL) briefly engage and disengage off-ball.
Banchero (ORL) brushes Doncic's (DAL) right arm and marginal contact occurs as Doncic drives inside the lane.
Anthony (ORL) steps slightly forward towards Green's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Banchero (ORL) releases his left hand away from Williams' (DAL) back and marginal contact occurs as the ball ricochets toward Banchero during the rebound.
Doncic (DAL) brushes Banchero's (ORL) right arm and marginal contact occurs as Banchero starts his dribble in the lane.
Lively II (DAL) is drawn into the air on the pump fake toward Banchero (ORL) and is not in a legal guarding position when body contact occurs during Banchero's upward shooting motion.
Banchero (ORL) brings his hands forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Doncic's (DAL) left arm as Doncic starts his dribble.
Banchero's (ORL) right arm comes forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Doncic's (DAL) side as Doncic elevates to pass.
Wagner (ORL) brings his left hand outward and marginal contact occurs with Lively II's (DAL) front as Lively II elevates to retrieve the pass.
Wagner (ORL) establishes himself in Williams' (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the screen.
Doncic (DAL) is extending slightly as he firms up over his left foot in Banchero's (ORL) path and marginal body contact occurs when they come together along the perimeter.
Ingles (ORL) and Hardaway Jr. (DAL) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Wagner (ORL) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Wagner (ORL) establishes a screening position in Williams' (DAL) path and and does not deliver contact during the pick.
Doncic (DAL) establishes verticality prior to incidental contact occurring with Wagner (ORL) during the driving shot attempt.
Ingles (ORL) brings his hands forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) front after Hardaway Jr. receives the inbound.
Wagner (ORL) brushes Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Wagner simultaneously makes contact with the ball.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) establishes his left foot as his pivot, and he lifts and re-plants it without releasing the ball.
Doncic (DAL) brushes Banchero's (ORL) left arm and Banchero is able to move through the marginal contact to finish at the rim.
Prior to the timeout being awarded, Banchero (ORL) and Doncic (DAL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Wagner (ORL) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL).
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) commits a take foul on Wagner (ORL).
Suggs (ORL) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL).
Green (DAL) commits a take foul on Banchero (ORL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Banchero's (ORL) right foot crosses over the plane of the free throw line prior to the releases his first free throw attempt.
Wagner (ORL) and Green (DAL) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Green (DAL) legally contests Wagner's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
